The -$62 is pure payoff asymmetry, which is BY DESIGN for a favorite-buyer:
avg loss **-$23.14** vs avg win **+$6.15**. Sum losses -$92.55, sum wins +$30.73, net -$61.82.
Breakeven win% for this payoff = **79.0%**; ETH's baseline 82% clears it by a hair, so any
sub-79% hour books a loss.

## Entry prices
Entries were normal, NOT clustered near the 0.85 ceiling: 0.76, 0.76, 0.80, 0.77, 0.79,
0.76, 0.84, 0.78, 0.76. Only one trade (round 15, @0.84) was near the top -- and it **won**.
The four losers entered at 0.76 / 0.80 / 0.77 / 0.79: middle-of-band, not thin-margin highs.

**Execution was clean -- zero slippage.** Every LIVE fill landed at the intended price to
4+ decimals (NO @ 0.7599999 vs intended 0.76; YES @ 0.7699999 vs 0.78 intended w/ book 0.77/0.78;
NO @ 0.84 vs intended 0.84). fill_price == intended_price across the board; no adverse fills.

## Spot context
Binance ETHUSDT 1-min, UTC 06:55-08:00:
open 1582.69, close 1580.67, **high 1584.90, low 1577.92**.
Total range **$6.98 = 0.44%**; net move **-$2.02 = -0.13%**. This is **flat chop**, not a
directional event -- ETH oscillated in a ~$5 band around 1580-1583 the entire hour.

That is precisely the regime that upsets 5-min favorites: with spot barely moving, the
side that closes the candle up-vs-down is a near coin-flip, yet the favorite is priced
0.76-0.84. Per losing round the deciding move was tiny:
- R9 settle 07:15: 07:10->07:15 close 1579.75->1581.83 (+$2.1 UP) flipped a NO bet.
- R10 settle 07:20: 1581.83->1580.53 (-$1.3 DOWN) flipped a YES bet.
- R11 settle 07:25: 1580.53->1580.28 (~$0.25, essentially flat) flipped a NO bet.
Sub-$2 wiggles on a $1580 tape decided every loss. No reversal, no trend, no news spike.

## vs normal
ETH baseline this dataset: **300/366 = 81.97%** win over ~8 hours. This hour: 55.6%.
Other ETH hours range 74.6%-93.8% win, with hourly pnl from -$145.87 to +$93.21 -- so
-$62 is **not even ETH's worst hour** (28th 07:00 was -$146; 29th 16:00 was -$96).
Binomial test at p=0.82: P(exactly 5/9) = 4.9%, **P(<=5 wins out of 9) = 6.2%**
(expected wins = 7.4). A ~1-in-16 hour. Across 8+ observed ETH hours you expect to draw
one like this. Uncommon, not anomalous; nowhere near a 3-sigma tail.
("fire 75%" = 9 traded of 12 rounds = 75% fire rate; 3 rounds correctly stood down. Normal.)

## Verdict: VARIANCE or SIGNAL
**VARIANCE.** Unlucky coin-flips at roughly fair odds. The evidence is clean on every
non-variance hypothesis:
- NOT concentrated: 4 independent ~-$23 losses, not one blow-up.
- NOT high entries: losers entered mid-band (0.76-0.80); the only 0.84 entry won.
- NOT execution: every LIVE fill = intended price, zero slippage, no adverse book.
- NOT a directional spot event: flat 0.44%-range chop, -0.13% net; losses came from
  sub-$2 wiggles flipping near-50/50 5-min outcomes.
The 55.6% result is within binomial noise of the 82% baseline (p=0.062). The big dollar
figure is just the structural -$23-loss / +$6-win asymmetry of buying favorites, amplified
by 4 losses landing in one hour.

## Action
**None required.** This is expected variance for a favorite-buying strategy; do not
re-tune off a single hour. One standing watch-item (not triggered by this hour): the
payoff math needs ~79% wins to break even and ETH sits at ~82%, a thin ~3pt margin.
That is a STRATEGY-LEVEL fragility (favorites in flat chop are marginally overpriced),
not a fault of this hour. If a real edge fix is wanted, it lives in entry-filtering for
low-volatility/chop regimes (skip when realized 5-min vol is tiny, since favorites are
most overpriced then) -- but that is a separate study, not an action item from -$62.
